# Student Performance Prediction Using Machine Learning

## Project Overview

This project aims to predict student examination scores using Machine Learning techniques. Various academic, behavioral, and socio-economic factors were analyzed to understand their impact on student performance.

The project follows the complete Machine Learning lifecycle, including data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and deployment.

---

## Dataset

Dataset Name: StudentPerformanceFactors.csv

Target Variable:

* Exam_Score

Important Features:

* Hours_Studied
* Attendance
* Sleep_Hours
* Previous_Scores
* Motivation_Level
* Teacher_Quality
* Family_Income
* Peer_Influence
* Access_to_Resources
* Distance_from_Home
* Gender

---

## Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

* Missing value handling
* Duplicate checking
* Ordinal encoding
* One-Hot Encoding
* Correlation analysis
* Feature selection

Missing values were handled in:

* Teacher_Quality
* Parental_Education_Level
* Distance_from_Home

---

## Feature Engineering

A new feature was created:

Study_Efficiency = Hours_Studied × Attendance

This feature combines study effort and attendance into a single meaningful metric.

---

## Machine Learning Models Used

1. Linear Regression
2. Random Forest Regressor
3. XGBoost Regressor

---

## Model Evaluation Results

| Model             | MAE    | MSE    | RMSE   | R² Score |
| ----------------- | ------ | ------ | ------ | -------- |
| Linear Regression | 0.4477 | 3.3309 | 1.8251 | 0.7721   |
| Random Forest     | 1.0804 | 4.8672 | 2.2062 | 0.6670   |
| XGBoost           | 0.9206 | 4.7942 | 2.1896 | 0.6720   |

### Final Selected Model

Linear Regression

Reason:

* Highest R² Score
* Lowest Prediction Error
* Best Overall Performance

---

## Deployment

The final model was saved using Joblib and deployed using Streamlit.

The application allows users to:

* Enter student information
* Generate real-time score predictions
* Interact through a simple web interface

